description:
Add graph data generation to the publisher.

## Implementation

1. In generator.py, after processing entries, build graph data:
   - nodes: [{id, label, path, category, tags}]
   - edges: [{source, target}] from resolved wikilinks

2. Write to output_dir/graph.json

## Data structure

```json
{
  "nodes": [
    {"id": "tooling/beads", "label": "Beads", "category": "tooling", "tags": ["git"]}
  ],
  "edges": [
    {"source": "tooling/beads", "target": "tooling/memex"}
  ]
}
```

Parent: voidlabs-kb-7jqq

LLM agents would benefit from a machine-readable dump of all mx commands, their parameters, types, and constraints.

**Proposal:** `mx schema` or `mx introspect` that outputs JSON:

```json
{
  "commands": {
    "add": {
      "description": "Create a new knowledge base entry",
      "params": {
        "title": {"type": "string", "required": true},
        "tags": {"type": "string", "required": true, "format": "comma-separated"},
        "category": {"type": "string", "required": "unless .kbcontext"},
        "content": {"type": "string", "required": "one of content/file/stdin/template"},
        ...
      },
      "examples": [...]
    }
  }
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Agents can programmatically understand available operations
- No need to parse --help text
- Can validate params before calling
- Enables tool-use schema generation
